subject: Track and Field
lead_paragraph: Dwain Chambers won the 60 meters at the European indoor championships in Turin, Italy, securing his first international title since coming back from a doping suspension. Chambers’s winning time, 6.46 seconds, fell short of the European indoor record of 6.42 he set Saturday.
